# =============================================================================
# .gigaignore for CaseScope
#
# Two jobs:
#   1. Strip the bulk Giga's defaults don't know about (case data, weights,
#      sibling repos, vendored binaries, rule packs).
#   2. RE-INCLUDE refactor source-of-truth docs that Giga's defaults silently
#      drop (*.md, *.txt, *.json, tests/, migrations/, docs/, wsgi.py).
#      Without these, the AI has no architectural context.
# =============================================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bulk strips (Giga's defaults don't cover these CaseScope-specific paths)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Runtime case data
staging/
storage/
uploads/
temp/
evidence/
evidence_uploads/
logs/
qdrant/
example_reports/
training_data/

# Model weights, training caches, GPU caches
lora_training/
local_models/
unsloth_compiled_cache/
.unsloth/
.triton/
.cache/
.nv/

# Bundled binaries / external runtimes
bin/EvtxECmd/
bin/chainsaw
bin/dotnet
bin/evtxecmd
bin/hayabusa
.dotnet/

# Detection rule packs (~10k YAML files, runtime data not source)
rules/hayabusa-rules/
rules/sigma/
rules/hayabusa/

# Sibling projects checked out alongside CaseScope
claude-code/
claw-code/

# Secrets and host config
.env
.env.*
license.json
.installation_id
.wget-hsts
ssl/
*.pem
*.key
*.crt

# OS / editor metadata
.cursor/
.cursorrules
.config/
__MACOSX/
.DS_Store

# Binary docs
*.docx
*.xlsx
*.pdf

# Large planning corpora that aren't the active source-of-truth
folder_tree.md
ai_report_summary.txt
dfir-model-comparison-a2-16gb.html
CaseScope_Enhanced_Analysis_System_Work_List.md
OpenCTI_Integration_Plan.md
enhance_ai.md


# =============================================================================
# RE-INCLUDES — these override Giga's default strips for files that ARE
# load-bearing for the refactor. Negation patterns (!) bring them back.
# =============================================================================

# Master refactor plan and origin transcripts
!_REFACTOR/
!_REFACTOR/**
!_REFACTOR/**/*.md

# Refactor source-of-truth contracts
!docs/
!docs/**
!docs/refactor/
!docs/refactor/**
!docs/refactor/*.md
!docs/refactor/*.csv
!docs/PARSERS.md
!docs/TIMEZONE.md
!docs/huntress_threat_intel_enrichment_plan.txt
!docs/ioc_model_comparison_2026-04-06.txt
!docs/ioc_provider_hardening_execution_plan.txt

# Top-level project state
!README.md
!version.json
!requirements.txt
!wsgi.py

# Phase regression tests — these LOCK the contracts that have been built
!tests/
!tests/**
!tests/*.py

# Schema history — informs Phase 7 work on what already exists
!migrations/
!migrations/*.py

# AI routing contracts (Phase 6 output)
!utils/ai_training/route_contracts.json
!utils/ai_training/local_model_targets.json
!utils/ai_training/global_examples.json
!utils/ai_training/hosted_provider_followup.txt
!utils/ai_training/modelfiles/
!utils/ai_training/modelfiles/*.Modelfile

# Bundled binary helper scripts (license generation, version files)
!bin/benchmark_embeddings.py
!bin/clear_cases.py
!bin/generate_license.py
!bin/generate_license_keypair.py
!bin/install_eztools.sh
!bin/install_hayabusa.sh
!bin/update_worker_concurrency.sh
!bin/hayabusa_version.txt
!bin/zeek_version.txt

# Refactor inventory script
!scripts/refactor/inventory_checks.py


# =============================================================================
# Expected result after this file is in place:
#
#   Files included: ~280 (200 source + ~80 reclaimed docs/tests/migrations)
#   Refactor context preserved:
#     ✓ _REFACTOR/master-goals-and-workstreams.plan.md
#     ✓ _REFACTOR/session-{a..f}.md
#     ✓ docs/refactor/finding_contract.md
#     ✓ docs/refactor/dispatch_state_machine.md
#     ✓ docs/refactor/agent_loop.md
#     ✓ docs/refactor/pattern_check_inventory.md (+ .csv)
#     ✓ docs/refactor/file_audit.md
#     ✓ docs/refactor/silent_default_audit.md
#     ✓ tests/test_phase{0..7}_*.py  (the contract regression locks)
#     ✓ migrations/*.py  (schema history)
#     ✓ version.json, requirements.txt, README.md, wsgi.py
#
# If 280 files busts the limit:
#   - Comment out the !_REFACTOR/session-*.md re-includes (transcripts only,
#     decisions are encoded in the master plan).
#   - Comment out the !tests/ re-includes (drops ~58 files; trade-off is
#     Giga loses regression context but keeps doc context, which matters more
#     for refactor work).
# =============================================================================